originalText.text: I went to try this deli sandwich shop in new york and it was okay. I wouldn't say it was worth the money. the lady charged me like.. $18 for a bag of chips and 1 chicken zesty lemon sandwich (with avocado, lettuce, onion, tomato, and balsamic vinegarette sauce). I would try their other sandwiches... but not sure if it's inflation or ny price. But the sandwich was just..OKAY :)

originalText.text:
Overpriced meals.
No competition with Columbia 1 Deli. Male staff workers aren't friendly and seem angry, most times.
Save your money. Better yet, for a scrumptious meal, walk one block south to Massawa Eritrean restaurant, sit down, and enjoy some homecooking for lunch or dinner, and everything is fresh.

Baba's novelty wore off. Steer clear.

originalText.text: Menus really need to be updated, with regards to people with food allergies. More considerations should be taken when called to fix an issue. Don't try to recharge for something that's paid for through an app. People should not have to pay for a mistake you have made. Very unprofessional. Don't recommend eating from here. I will never again. Praying I don't have an issue because of my food allergies. Wild.

originalText.text: So far, so good. Sandwiches at the deli are delicious, but you may want to check what they are charging you with the menu. Clearly because this place is brand new, they are getting staff from other bodegas further downtown, who charge what they expect the sandwich to cost rather than what it says in the menu. All good if you’re looking for it, though, because your charges come up on a screen as they ring you up, so everything is transparent, a rarity at bodegas around here. Either way, I’m ecstatic to have this 24-hour option nearby. Columbia deli’s monopoly is no more.
